    {"question_text": "What does this ETag-based incremental scraping code accomplish?\n\nimport requests, json\n\ndef fetch_if_modified(url, etag_cache='etags.json'):\n    etags = json.load(open(etag_cache)) if os.path.exists(etag_cache) else {}\n    headers = {}\n    if url in etags:\n        headers['If-None-Match'] = etags[url]\n    resp = requests.get(url, headers=headers)\n    if resp.status_code == 304:\n        return None  # Not modified\n    etags[url] = resp.headers.get('ETag', '')\n    json.dump(etags, open(etag_cache, 'w'))\n    return resp.text", "option_a": "It always downloads the full page regardless of changes", "option_b": "It skips downloading if the page hasn't changed since last fetch, saving bandwidth", "option_c": "It caches the entire response in memory", "option_d": "It validates the page content using checksums", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "web_scraping"},
