    {"question_text": "What does this middleware pattern accomplish in Scrapy?\n\nclass ProxyMiddleware:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.proxies = ['http://p1:8080', 'http://p2:8080']\n        self.current = 0\n    \n    def process_request(self, request, spider):\n        request.meta['proxy'] = self.proxies[self.current % len(self.proxies)]\n        self.current += 1", "option_a": "It validates proxies before use", "option_b": "It rotates through a list of proxy servers for each outgoing request", "option_c": "It blocks requests through proxies", "option_d": "It only uses the first proxy", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "web_scraping"},
