    {"question_text": "What does this code pattern accomplish for deduplication during scraping?\n\nimport hashlib\n\nclass Deduplicator:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.seen = set()\n    \n    def is_duplicate(self, item):\n        key = hashlib.md5(json.dumps(item, sort_keys=True).encode()).hexdigest()\n        if key in self.seen:\n            return True\n        self.seen.add(key)\n        return False", "option_a": "It encrypts items for security", "option_b": "It creates a hash fingerprint of each item to detect and skip duplicates efficiently", "option_c": "It validates data integrity", "option_d": "It compresses items for storage", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "web_scraping"},
