    {"question_text": "What does this async scraping pattern with rate limiting achieve?\n\nimport asyncio\nimport aiohttp\n\nasync def throttled_fetch(session, url, delay=1.0):\n    await asyncio.sleep(delay)\n    async with session.get(url) as resp:\n        return await resp.text()\n\nasync def main(urls):\n    async with aiohttp.ClientSession() as session:\n        tasks = [throttled_fetch(session, url, i * 0.5) for i, url in enumerate(urls)]\n        return await asyncio.gather(*tasks)", "option_a": "It staggers requests with increasing delays to distribute load over time", "option_b": "It makes all requests simultaneously", "option_c": "It retries all failed requests", "option_d": "It blocks all requests", "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "web_scraping"},
    {"question_text": "What does this Scrapy signal handler do?\n\nfrom scrapy import signals\n\nclass StatsCollector:\n    @classmethod\n    def from_crawler(cls, crawler):\n        ext = cls()\n        crawler.signals.connect(ext.spider_closed, signal=signals.spider_closed)\n        return ext\n    \n    def spider_closed(self, spider):\n        stats = spider.crawler.stats.get_stats()\n        spider.logger.info(f'Total items: {stats.get(\"item_scraped_count\", 0)}')", "option_a": "It starts a new spider when one closes", "option_b": "It logs the total scraped item count when the spider finishes", "option_c": "It prevents the spider from closing", "option_d": "It resets statistics during scraping", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "web_scraping"},
    {"question_text": "What does this code pattern accomplish for handling different response content types?\n\ndef parse_response(resp):\n    content_type = resp.headers.get('Content-Type', '')\n    if 'application/json' in content_type:\n        return resp.json()\n    elif 'text/html' in content_type:\n        return BeautifulSoup(resp.text, 'html.parser')\n    elif 'text/xml' in content_type or 'application/xml' in content_type:\n        return BeautifulSoup(resp.text, 'xml')\n    else:\n        return resp.text", "option_a": "It only handles JSON responses", "option_b": "It converts all responses to HTML", "option_c": "It routes response parsing based on Content-Type header, using appropriate parsers for each type", "option_d": "It validates response encoding", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "web_scraping"},
