    {"question_text": "What does this error handling pattern accomplish for robust scraping?\n\nfrom requests.exceptions import RequestException, Timeout, ConnectionError\n\ndef robust_fetch(url, max_retries=3):\n    for attempt in range(max_retries):\n        try:\n            resp = requests.get(url, timeout=(3.05, 27))\n            resp.raise_for_status()\n            return resp\n        except Timeout:\n            if attempt == max_retries - 1: raise\n            time.sleep(2 ** attempt)\n        except ConnectionError:\n            if attempt == max_retries - 1: raise\n            time.sleep(5)\n        except RequestException as e:\n            raise\n    return None", "option_a": "It retries only on timeouts and connection errors with different wait strategies, but fails fast on other errors", "option_b": "It retries all errors equally", "option_c": "It never raises exceptions", "option_d": "It only handles Timeout errors", "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "web_scraping"},
